This was easy and delicious. Like other reviewers suggested, I marinated the chicken in lemon juice, red pepper flakes, cracked black pepper and a teeny bit of thyme....I think I threw a touch of garlic powder in there too. I made the relish as directed.

Rating: 4
I read many of the reviews and - because of personal choices - I didn't use any olive oil in the roasting of the corn, I just sprayed the pan with some olive oil spray. I also added the juice of 1 lemon (and the zest of half of same) to brighten the flavors a little bit. LOVELY! I will definitely make it again.

Rating: 4
The relish was delicious, although I added a bit of vinegar and roasted the tomatoes. It has a lot of flavor, but not quite enough to make up for the blandness of the chicken in the recipe. The second time I made it I marinated the chicken in lemon juice and added red pepper and a few dried herbs to the flour, which made this much better.

