Rating: 3
We loved the fresh tastes and the light feel of the flavors. Found it easy to make and quick, which comes in handy. The relish benefits from the generous use of salt and pepper.

Rating: 3
We think this is a nice, light summer recipe and a great way to use what's fresh in the vegetable garden, if you have one. It just needs a bit of a tune-up. I use chicken tenders for this recipe. Cuts out the need for pounding. Also, I've found that dredging the chicken in my favorite oyster breading, which is more highly seasoned than flour alone, adds a lot of flavor. Make sure to get good, ripe tomatoes, fresh-as-possible sweet corn, and high-quality olive oil for best flavor with the relish. And don't be shy with the salt and pepper.

